  <channel>
    <title>What do warriors "need" and "want"?</title>
    <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&amp;message.id=15373</link>
    <description>&lt;div&gt;Since the couple other long threads at the top of this forum have regressed to the point no one wants to actually &amp;quot;discuss&amp;quot; anything in lieu of insults, hyperbole, and gross generalizations, I thought I'd start a new thread.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;-----------&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;A) TANKING&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;a) 1h/shield - Obviously a big issue with many warriors, so let's start here.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;What are the perceived problems that have been raised?&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;1) Maintaining aggro&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;2) DPS loss&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;3) Loss in &amp;quot;tanking&amp;quot; advantage over knights who are using 1h/shield because points 1 and 2 make 1h/shield an unviable day to day solution&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;So my question here is, what do warriors envision a *feasible* solution is (use your opinion on what feasible means I guess, even though we all know there are knights and warriors that are completely ridiculous in their requests and expectations)?&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;What is an acceptable dps loss from dual wield and 2h fighting to use a 1h/shield set up?&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;What is needed in order to allow aggro to be maintained day to day in the 1h/shield set up? A feasibility caveat here would have to be something that didn't trivialize aggro in other set ups such that tank switching becomes super easy on raids, as apparently SoE finds a need to give warriors less than stellar aggro as some sort of raid strategy or some junk.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;What is an acceptable gap in tanking ability between warriors and knights? And don't through out some junk number, I want to know in given situations, because different situations are different.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;For example, if the dps taken difference is due to better warrior MITIGATION then the higher the gear level (i.e. ac) then the % advantage will get lower and lower the better your gear or the weaker the mob.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;When offering solutions (better itemization for warrior specific gear? better return on raw ac? higher skill caps (presumably possible in code now)) think about the effect on differing levels of play. Talking about what the difference is right now between different levels of play is good too, because maybe its ok if something disproportionately helps one end of the scale.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;b) Endurance Regen&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Not much to say about this, its insane they they haven't done anything about this, as there are a ton of things they could do to fix this &amp;quot;problem&amp;quot; in a matter of days, which begs the question of whether the devs simply do not want warriors to have good aggro control.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;B) DPS&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;1) Dual wield weapon ratios haven't scaled as well as 2h ratios for warriors&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;2) General dps advantage relative to knights has degraded as a consequence of this and itemization (warriors mainhanding bbob you're going to have to expect the dps gap to be degraded when knights are upgrading)&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;3) Paladin Vanquish Undead aa gives them unfair dps advantage against undead&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;I'm a paladin, let me say that these are things I've seen raised in a level-headed (sometimes) fashion on these boards and by people I know. Obviously, I love vanquish and don't see a problem with it, *many* warriors do. I am not a fan of addition by subtraction when it comes to a game like this, in most cases I'd prefer to give other classes something to compensate (wouldn't hurt my feelings to give warriors an aa ability that gave them &amp;quot;slays&amp;quot; versus some other type of mob). My opinion on that issue out in the open.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;---------------------------&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Look, it is apparent to any reasonable person that warriors are supposed to take less dps than knights and are supposed to do more melee dps. But, there is a lot of room for *reasoned* discussion on the particulars and where those gaps should be.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;So it would be nice to do without the flames, and get some concrete opinions on what these gaps *should* be and where they currently are, and how changes could be implemented to accomplish going from where they are to where they should be. I know there are issues I missed, so bring them up to. I'm absolutely sick of all the ranting and whining and hyperbole going on in this forum (and anywhere else knight/warrior issues come up), so it would be real nice if this didn't regress either. It is hard to lock on to what warriors &amp;quot;need&amp;quot; when the vast majority of posts are by a handful of people that spend an inordinate amount of those posts complaining in generalized terms.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
    <pubDate>Tue, 14 Mar 2006 22:59:01 GMT</pubDate>
    <managingEditor>Abazzagaroth</managingEditor>
    <dc:creator>Abazzagaroth</dc:creator>
    <dc:date>2006-03-14T22:59:01Z</dc:date>
    <item>
      <title>What do warriors "need" and "want"?</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&amp;message.id=15373#M15373</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;Since the couple other long threads at the top of this forum have regressed to the point no one wants to actually &amp;quot;discuss&amp;quot; anything in lieu of insults, hyperbole, and gross generalizations, I thought I'd start a new thread.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;-----------&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;A) TANKING&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;a) 1h/shield - Obviously a big issue with many warriors, so let's start here.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;What are the perceived problems that have been raised?&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;1) Maintaining aggro&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;2) DPS loss&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;3) Loss in &amp;quot;tanking&amp;quot; advantage over knights who are using 1h/shield because points 1 and 2 make 1h/shield an unviable day to day solution&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;So my question here is, what do warriors envision a *feasible* solution is (use your opinion on what feasible means I guess, even though we all know there are knights and warriors that are completely ridiculous in their requests and expectations)?&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;What is an acceptable dps loss from dual wield and 2h fighting to use a 1h/shield set up?&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;What is needed in order to allow aggro to be maintained day to day in the 1h/shield set up? A feasibility caveat here would have to be something that didn't trivialize aggro in other set ups such that tank switching becomes super easy on raids, as apparently SoE finds a need to give warriors less than stellar aggro as some sort of raid strategy or some junk.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;What is an acceptable gap in tanking ability between warriors and knights? And don't through out some junk number, I want to know in given situations, because different situations are different.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;For example, if the dps taken difference is due to better warrior MITIGATION then the higher the gear level (i.e. ac) then the % advantage will get lower and lower the better your gear or the weaker the mob.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;When offering solutions (better itemization for warrior specific gear? better return on raw ac? higher skill caps (presumably possible in code now)) think about the effect on differing levels of play. Talking about what the difference is right now between different levels of play is good too, because maybe its ok if something disproportionately helps one end of the scale.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;b) Endurance Regen&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Not much to say about this, its insane they they haven't done anything about this, as there are a ton of things they could do to fix this &amp;quot;problem&amp;quot; in a matter of days, which begs the question of whether the devs simply do not want warriors to have good aggro control.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;B) DPS&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;1) Dual wield weapon ratios haven't scaled as well as 2h ratios for warriors&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;2) General dps advantage relative to knights has degraded as a consequence of this and itemization (warriors mainhanding bbob you're going to have to expect the dps gap to be degraded when knights are upgrading)&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;3) Paladin Vanquish Undead aa gives them unfair dps advantage against undead&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;I'm a paladin, let me say that these are things I've seen raised in a level-headed (sometimes) fashion on these boards and by people I know. Obviously, I love vanquish and don't see a problem with it, *many* warriors do. I am not a fan of addition by subtraction when it comes to a game like this, in most cases I'd prefer to give other classes something to compensate (wouldn't hurt my feelings to give warriors an aa ability that gave them &amp;quot;slays&amp;quot; versus some other type of mob). My opinion on that issue out in the open.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;---------------------------&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Look, it is apparent to any reasonable person that warriors are supposed to take less dps than knights and are supposed to do more melee dps. But, there is a lot of room for *reasoned* discussion on the particulars and where those gaps should be.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;So it would be nice to do without the flames, and get some concrete opinions on what these gaps *should* be and where they currently are, and how changes could be implemented to accomplish going from where they are to where they should be. I know there are issues I missed, so bring them up to. I'm absolutely sick of all the ranting and whining and hyperbole going on in this forum (and anywhere else knight/warrior issues come up), so it would be real nice if this didn't regress either. It is hard to lock on to what warriors &amp;quot;need&amp;quot; when the vast majority of posts are by a handful of people that spend an inordinate amount of those posts complaining in generalized terms.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
