    <item>
      <title>Re: What do warriors "need" and "want"?</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&amp;message.id=24901#M24901</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
Abazzagaroth wrote:&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Since the couple other long threads at the top of this forum have regressed to the point no one wants to actually "discuss" anything in lieu of insults, hyperbole, and gross generalizations, I thought I'd start a new thread.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;-----------&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;A) TANKING&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;a) 1h/shield - Obviously a big issue with many warriors, so let's start here.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;What are the perceived problems that have been raised?&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;1) Maintaining aggro&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;2) DPS loss&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;3) Loss in "tanking" advantage over knights who are using 1h/shield because points 1 and 2 make 1h/shield an unviable day to day solution&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;So my question here is, what do warriors envision a *feasible* solution is (use your opinion on what feasible means I guess, even though we all know there are knights and warriors that are completely ridiculous in their requests and expectations)?&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;What is an acceptable dps loss from dual wield and 2h fighting to use a 1h/shield set up?&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;What is needed in order to allow aggro to be maintained day to day in the 1h/shield set up? A feasibility caveat here would have to be something that didn't trivialize aggro in other set ups such that tank switching becomes super easy on raids, as apparently SoE finds a need to give warriors less than stellar aggro as some sort of raid strategy or some junk.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;What is an acceptable gap in tanking ability between warriors and knights? And don't through out some junk number, I want to know in given situations, because different situations are different.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;For example, if the dps taken difference is due to better warrior MITIGATION then the higher the gear level (i.e. ac) then the % advantage will get lower and lower the better your gear or the weaker the mob.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;When offering solutions (better itemization for warrior specific gear? better return on raw ac? higher skill caps (presumably possible in code now)) think about the effect on differing levels of play. Talking about what the difference is right now between different levels of play is good too, because maybe its ok if something disproportionately helps one end of the scale.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;b) Endurance Regen&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Not much to say about this, its insane they they haven't done anything about this, as there are a ton of things they could do to fix this "problem" in a matter of days, which begs the question of whether the devs simply do not want warriors to have good aggro control.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;B) DPS&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;1) Dual wield weapon ratios haven't scaled as well as 2h ratios for warriors&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;2) General dps advantage relative to knights has degraded as a consequence of this and itemization (warriors mainhanding bbob you're going to have to expect the dps gap to be degraded when knights are upgrading)&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;3) Paladin Vanquish Undead aa gives them unfair dps advantage against undead&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;U&gt;A. 1. Tanking - Maintaining aggro, loss of dps, 1h/shield tanking....&lt;/U&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Ok. Warriors taunts are timed like 1 minute between. Paladins use a stun which virtually recycle immediately. Warriors Endurance regens very slowly. Mana items are plentiful which increase mana regen. So basiclally Paladins ability to generate high speed long term taunting is unlimited. Shadow Knight us mana too, so same thing. And they get the same level basic taunt as warriors. Warriors have had the discipline taunts added but not a real improvement because we are severaly limited by endurance.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Ever notice that there doesn't seem to be any mobs in Norath that don't resist the stunning portion of our taunts? PTA, COC even anger/eb procs. I have never seen any mob not resist this. &lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Loss of DPS? - The biggest problem for warriors is that we get an upgrade to our primary weapon every 4 or 5 expansions. I'm still using BoBB and I'm kill Mayong weekly and am in Deathknell. Why? Becase every expansion since Velious SOE has created class specific weapons for knights. The alternative weapons are kind of suck in my opinion.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Have you also noticed there's a whole lot more Undead stuff in the game now? Basically they are tailoring the game for knights. Granted live or undead warrior dps remains the same. So do our weapons. They seldom change.&amp;nbsp;It would have been great for our epics to be something more usefull then a permanent off hand weapon. But SOE chose to make our weapon useless. &lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Basically warriors in EQ are an after thought. &lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;1h/Shields - 1 suck alternatives for 1 hand weapons plus the shield's aggro proc doesn't work.&amp;nbsp; I seldom use a shield. There are very few mobs which warrant it's use. They need to consider putting in a double(triple) bash aaxp&amp;nbsp;like double riposte have a chance to swing more then one time. Fix the shield proc to actually generate aggro. &lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;The biggest thing to help warriors with aggro is getting the rest of the raid to practice raid skills 101 and control their own aggro. &lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;U&gt;Endurance Regen&lt;/U&gt; - i've talked about this. I click off SA 100 times an hour. Seems like if it's going to always be a nuisance to me how about we give it an endurance regen component. Not going to happen becuase SOE will never do anything positive for warriors.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;U&gt;DPS -&lt;/U&gt; The game is being slanted toward knights in the way of weapons. Every expansion SOE pulls out at least 1 knight specific weapon per high end zone. Same with monks, beastlords, rogues and bards. All these classes get upgrades and improvements. Warriors get the choice of fighting over weapons which anybody can use. Well the anybody can use weapons are not replacements to class specific weapons. &lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;How about disciplines? &lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;I still use defensive and evasive. I haven't used anything else since they come up when I tank. I popped on Stonewall a few times but you see you get snared with that one. So backing up is impossible. The other problem with it is, if the npc casts a snare spell on you, the defensive effects are negated. You're left double snared, getting hit for full damage and losing endurance. But hey warriors don't fret, we'll give you a high end taunt which is actually a dot which uses 3 times the amount of endurance as a knight's mana using&amp;nbsp;stun spell uses. Well I hope not knight is actually stunning when a warrior is supposed to be on a named.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Don't you think in 15 levels+ warriors would be just about due for something kind of real upgrade? If we aren't going to get a new discipline then how about giving&amp;nbsp;warriorrs at least and AAXPs to increase their dps during using either and/or aaxps to increase their duration or mitigation? Maybe even aaxps to reduce the recycle time? Apparently Evasive and Defensive are our baseline tanking disciplines. Seems to me we should get better over time.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;How about more dps type skills? Or maybe aaxps to increase their duration?&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffff00&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Well anyway, it is pointless to say anything in a thread that's 10+ pages long.&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffff00&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;U&gt;&amp;nbsp;Even more pointless to say anything to SOE about doing something to improve warriors.&lt;/U&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;</description>
