&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;BR&gt;There are a few things that you did overlook a bit in why things are the way they are.&amp;nbsp; You brought up bards and rogues as sharing weapons that are BRD/ROG only.&amp;nbsp; This is rather common in a lot of things with those two.&amp;nbsp; They share gear that is similarily bard/rogue, as well as weaponry.&amp;nbsp; Granted the game has moved a bit away from the shared gear, but the weapons remain the same.&amp;nbsp; This is also very similar with H2H and Blunt weapons for monks and beastlords.&amp;nbsp; They share a very similar weapon set and gear set... shouldn't be a surprise.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;The one point that I will say that you have a point on is that Warriors generally do not get their own class only type weapon lately.&amp;nbsp; This, however, as posted by a dev, is backlash of the added utility you guys recieved in the Bazu line of agro generation.&amp;nbsp; Do I see this as right?&amp;nbsp; No.&amp;nbsp; Warriors deserve their own class weapons similar to everyone else, but the down side is that they will end up very similar in ratio to other 1h weapons you already weild.&amp;nbsp; One thing no warrior seems to notice is that knights take a huge hit to dps switching to 1handers over adequate, similar level 2handers.&amp;nbsp; There is an astronomical difference between the dps our 1.5 does and Hopebringer.&amp;nbsp; There is a huge difference between our 2.0 and Blade of Forgotten Faith.&amp;nbsp; This is due in a large part to the fact that our AAs are geared to two hander use and they do not work on one hand weapons at all.&amp;nbsp; Though for 1handers they look like they have stellar and insane ratios... those ratios don't equate to much in a Knight's hands.&amp;nbsp; Then again... where are the complaints that casters have 24/24 ratio weapons with 854 dd procs that are purchasable in the bazaar or easily obtained?&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;I play a 70/1k+ Paladin.&amp;nbsp; I do ask this... where is all of this magical undead you speak of?&amp;nbsp; Let's see here, at lvl 70, if I want to exp off of undead I have the choice of 70.X missions, a few other random missions, and Ruins of Illsalin.&amp;nbsp; In prophecy, there is the Arcstone dead, which are pointless for me to hunt with a group as they are solo material thus a waste of time for me to group for.&amp;nbsp; I saw some undead in devastation.. but in trying to exp there, it is not even close to a fun place to hunt.&amp;nbsp; One too many times have my groups been clipped by a roaming army.&amp;nbsp; If the undead take over Rage, thats another zone.&amp;nbsp; However, I have seen that scenario once since PoR has been live.&amp;nbsp; There are undead in ToB also, but it's an insane place to exp and the rewards just are not worth it in the end.&amp;nbsp; Yes, there is a decent amount of undead, but it tailors to clerics and necros as well.&amp;nbsp; Never mind that clerics do have an AA DoT that can do 32k damage.&amp;nbsp; Oh yeah, and having a zone of pure undead makes it a viable place for a necro to be group friendly if slowers aren't too available, along with having mezzes and other nice tools for undead.&amp;nbsp; But yes, once again, let's focus on the fact that Paladin utility is the only thing worth mentioning in the same breath as undead.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;One last thing to add to this... how many groups do you actually see in Illsalin exping on a day to day basis?&amp;nbsp; One, maybe?&amp;nbsp; Ironic.. for as powerful as VU3 is touted to be... how come no one is taking Paladins there in droves and exploiting it?&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;I agree full well that warriors need a boost, that endurance needs to be unbroken.&amp;nbsp; However, you also made a comment in the cost differences... let me ask this, What does your melee agro cost you?&amp;nbsp; Nothing.&amp;nbsp; Do you realize that Paladins chain stunning costs roughly the same throughout a fight as bazu?&amp;nbsp; Generally the result is the same, some dumb DPS class will inevitably steal agro.&amp;nbsp; This happens to Knights and Warriors alike.&amp;nbsp; While I agree that endurance needs endurance regen similar to mana regen, the funny part is that once again, we have another Warrior wanting to have the exact same things as casters, only with a yellow bar instead of blue.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;When you state Resist, do you mean Resist or Immune?&amp;nbsp; There are tons of mobs in the high end exp game that are even immune to Paladin stuns.&amp;nbsp; There are few they take hold on, and as you mentioned undead earlier... all undead in DoD and PoR are unstunable no matter what level they are.&amp;nbsp; Even so, if it's resisted or immune, it matters not as they still generate agro just the same.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;As for Defensive/Evasive... They have been upgraded, but you know... if they were not as powerful as they were when they came out... don't you think they would have been made more powerful yet?&amp;nbsp; Somehow Defensive seems far more powerful now days than it did versus Nagafen... I wonder why that is.&amp;nbsp; You got new lines added... rampage and ae taunt and incite/bazu line.&amp;nbsp; They haven't upgraded Evasive or Defensive... they haven't upgraded CH either and that's been around longer than defensive.&amp;nbsp; Is there any sense in that either?&lt;/P&gt;</description>
